		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31876785">An atrocious movie which destroyed the character development of the original series and replaced the complex themes of the original series (namely, selflessness vs selfishness) with yuri pandering and a bloody cake scene. It's Urobuchi at his worst.<br />
A lot of events felt forced and the movie told its story rather than showing it, and expects us to accept its turn of events as something other than a glorious comedy.<br />
Interesting ideas, no doubt, but pathetic execution. I'm pretending it never happened.</div><div style="margin-top: 8px;"><em>Modified by sushiisawesome, 06-23-14, 2:06 AM</em></div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://i.imgur.com/8NuZt.png" /></div></td>
