		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31923437">One of the terrible parts of the movie concerns with how Urobuchi deals with exposition, having a very &quot;tell-don't-show&quot; philosophy with it. I'm OK with the movie throwing us into a new world with new rules for the sake of grabbing our attention and throwing us off-balance, but he chose the worst possible way to deal with it i.e. <div class="spoiler"><input type="button" class="button" onClick="this.nextSibling.nextSibling.style.display='block';this.style.display='none';" value="Show spoiler"> <span class="spoiler_content" style="display:none"><input type="button" class="button" onClick="this.parentNode.style.display='none';this.parentNode.parentNode.childNodes[0].style.display='block';" value="Hide spoiler"><br>Kyuubey delivering a 7-minute monologue straight-up telling us what the fuck has been happening for the past hour and why. There's some snappy Shinbo-visuals and Homura's pissed-off actions against Kyuubey that occur for the sake of spicing things up, but that doesn't change the fact that we're listening to Kato Emiri read a dozen pages of script to us. <!--spoiler--></span></div></div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
