		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31925567">Prettiest anime of the last year by a large margin&mdash;they had the money and they had the will.<br />
<br />
A lot of people have calledt it overly stylized, but the art direction actually makes perfect sense in the context of the story. Half of what is told is done so visually, stylistically, and choreographically. Considering this, I don't see where the &quot;tell show whatever whatever&quot; comes from.<br />
<br />
Don't know how I feel about Nagisa/Charlotte. Charlotte was easily one of the most creative and interesting witches in the television series and Nagisa's character design in the movie is great, but her inclusion didn't seem to serve any real purpose other than to create even more opportunities to make the anime pretty.<br />
<br />
Unsure how I feel about the story as a whole. Perhaps there was more there than was necessary, but you also don't want an Utena movie situation there's no glue to hold your spectacle together. Some were upset by and/or otherwise unsatisfied with the ending, but honestly, this isn't the type of work that befits a nice, tidy conclusion. (For the record, it wasn't Urobuchi's idea.) Wasn't phased by &quot;yuri pandering.&quot;[1]<br />
<br />
Cake scene was awesome kids just don't know how to appreciate a cake scene these days.<br />
